The mode is changed by the occurrance of two successive
.I case
control characters.
.
Two
.FONT CR circumflexes
.FONT CB ^^
cause the mode to be set to
.IR "upper case" ,
and two
.FONT CR back\-slashes
.FONT CB "\[rs]\[rs]"
cause the mode to be set to
.IR "lower case" .
.
.
.P
The use of the above corresponds to the use of the
.FONT CR shift
and
.FONT CR shift\-lock
keys on a typewriter.
